HEADWORD: collared lizard
<hw>col"lared liz"ard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of
several species of lizards of the genus <gen>Crotaphytus</gen> and the
family <fam>Iguanidae</fam>, of the central and western U.S. and
northern Mexico, having long tails and usually bearing markings on the
neck appearing like a collar of two black bands.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

